import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='value', hue='variable', data=pd.melt(data, ['date']))
    chart.set(xlabel='Date', ylabel='Count')
    chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    chart.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of injuries and diseases during the Crimean War?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wounds', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Wounds')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wounds during the Crimean War?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('date').mean().reset_index()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='date', y='value', hue='variable', data=pd.melt(data, ['date']))
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average number of injuries and diseases per day during the Crimean War?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['total_injuries'] = data['wounds'] + data['other'] + data['disease']
    injury_types = ['wounds', 'other']
    injury_counts = [data[injury_type].sum() for injury_type in injury_types]
    injury_percentages = [count / sum(injury_counts) for count in injury_counts]
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.pie(injury_percentages, labels=injury_types, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the most common type of injury during the Crimean War?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
